## 1. Platform Overview

**LabProject** is a production-grade medical laboratory information management system (LIMS) extended with a white-label, multi-provider AI interpretation layer. It manages the complete clinical test lifecycle — from patient registration and test ordering through sample processing, result entry, AI-assisted interpretation, and final report delivery.

**Platform evolution from migrations:**

| Era | Period | Focus |
|---|---|---|
| Core LIMS | Jun 2020 – Nov 2021 | Patients, tests, cultures, doctors, billing, reporting |
| AI Layer | Feb 10, 2026 | AI providers, interpretations, patient subscriptions, payments |
| External Reports | Feb 11, 2026 | Upload and AI analysis of external lab PDFs |
| Doctor Wallet | Feb 11, 2026 | Commission rules, ledgers, payout requests |
| Appointments | Feb 11, 2026 | Scheduling, availability, resources, reminders, triage |

The platform was built in 2020–2021 as a standard LIMS, then received a **complete AI and commercial feature overhaul in February 2026** — all within a single 19-day engineering sprint (Feb 8–Feb 26).

