## 4. AI Provider Governance

### `token_costs` JSON field

The `token_costs` column allows per-provider cost tracking without schema migrations when pricing changes:

```json
{
  "input_per_1k":  0.00015,
  "output_per_1k": 0.00060
}
```

This enables `ai_usage_logs.cost_estimate` to be calculated dynamically based on the active provider's pricing at the time of each call.

### `monthly_caps` JSON field

```json
{
  "hard_cap_usd":  50.00,
  "soft_warn_usd": 40.00
}
```

Admins can set spend ceilings per provider. When a cap is hit, the system routes automatically to the next `failover_order` provider — a critical governance control for a platform where AI costs scale with patient volume.

### AI Usage Log (`ai_usage_logs`)

```sql
CREATE TABLE `ai_usage_logs` (
  `patient_id`    bigint UNSIGNED,  -- Links to patient record
  `provider`      varchar(191),     -- Which provider served the request
  `model`         varchar(191),     -- Exact model used
  `prompt_type`   varchar(191),     -- Type of AI call (interpretation, summary, etc.)
  `tokens_in`     int UNSIGNED,     -- Input token count
  `tokens_out`    int UNSIGNED,     -- Output token count
  `cost_estimate` decimal(10,4),    -- Computed cost at request time
  `latency_ms`    int UNSIGNED,     -- Response time in milliseconds
  `status`        varchar(191),     -- ok / error / timeout
  `consent_at`    timestamp         -- Timestamp of patient consent
);
```

This table enables: provider cost dashboards, latency benchmarking across models, per-patient AI spend attribution, and consent audit trails — all critical for a compliant medical AI deployment.

