## 5. Clinical Interpretation Pipeline

### How AI integrates into the test result lifecycle

```
Patient Registered
       │
       ▼
Test Ordered  (groups + group_tests)
       │
       ▼
Results Entered  (group_test_results)
       │
       ▼
AI Interpretation Triggered
       │                        │
       ▼                        ▼
ai_interpretations       ai_interpretation_markers
  result_id                marker_name
  patient_id               value
  provider_ref             reference_range
  model_ref                explanation (per-marker AI text)
  summary (narrative)
  status_indicators (JSON)
  disclaimer (mandatory)
  cache_ttl
       │
       ▼
Patient Report Generated (AI summary + mandatory disclaimer)
       │
       ▼
ai_usage_logs (cost + consent + latency recorded)
```

### `ai_interpretations` — holistic summary

```sql
CREATE TABLE `ai_interpretations` (
  `result_id`         bigint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,  -- FK to group_test_results
  `patient_id`        bigint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
  `provider_ref`      varchar(191),              -- e.g. 'openai'
  `model_ref`         varchar(191),              -- e.g. 'gpt-4o-mini'
  `summary`           longtext,                  -- AI-generated narrative
  `status_indicators` json,                      -- Flagged markers (high/low/critical)
  `disclaimer`        text,                      -- Non-diagnostic disclaimer
  `generated_at`      timestamp,
  `cache_ttl`         int UNSIGNED               -- Seconds to cache (0 = no cache)
);
```

### `ai_interpretation_markers` — per-marker explanations

```sql
CREATE TABLE `ai_interpretation_markers` (
  `interpretation_id` bigint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
  `marker_name`       varchar(191),   -- e.g. 'Hemoglobin', 'WBC', 'Creatinine'
  `value`             varchar(191),   -- Patient's actual result value
  `reference_range`   varchar(191),   -- Normal range for context
  `explanation`       longtext        -- AI explanation of this specific marker
);
```

This design separates the holistic summary from marker-level explanations — allowing the UI to render granular "what does this value mean?" tooltips alongside the overall interpretation narrative.

### External Report AI Analysis (`patient_external_reports`)

The platform ingests external lab PDFs and runs AI analysis on them too:

```sql
CREATE TABLE `patient_external_reports` (
  `original_filename` varchar(191),
  `mime_type`         varchar(191),
  `size_bytes`        bigint UNSIGNED,
  `text_content`      longtext,       -- Extracted text from PDF
  `parsed_json`       json,           -- Structured parse output
  `status`            varchar(191),   -- pending_extraction / extracted / failed
  `ai_summary`        longtext,       -- AI narrative of external report
  `last_summary_at`   timestamp
);
```

This creates a unified AI analysis layer across both internal lab results and external reports the patient brings in — a longitudinal health intelligence capability.

