## 8. Appointment and Scheduling Intelligence

The appointments schema extends well beyond a simple booking calendar.

### Full Appointment Lifecycle State Machine

```sql
`status`                 -- requested / confirmed / cancelled / completed
`triage_used`            -- Was AI triage applied? (tinyint)
`triage_urgency`         -- low / medium / high / critical
`checkin_status`         -- arrived / in_room / done / no_show
`arrived_at`             -- Physical arrival timestamp
`in_room_at`             -- Room entry timestamp
`done_at`                -- Completion timestamp
`no_show_at`             -- No-show detection timestamp
`calendar_provider`      -- google / microsoft (external sync)
`calendar_event_id`      -- External calendar event ID
`deposit_amount`         -- Pre-payment amount
`deposit_status`         -- paid / waived / refunded
`deposit_transaction_id` -- FK to payment_transactions
```

These timestamps enable: wait time analysis (`arrived_at` → `in_room_at`), treatment duration (`in_room_at` → `done_at`), no-show rate tracking, and deposit collection funnel analysis.

### Covering Index Strategy

```sql
KEY `appointments_doctor_branch_time_status_idx`
    (doctor_id, branch_id, scheduled_at, status)
```

This is a **covering index** for the most common availability query: "find all non-cancelled appointments for doctor X at branch Y on date Z" — no additional column lookups required after the index scan.

### Resource Conflict Prevention

```sql
-- resource_reservations
KEY `resv_idx` (resource_id, start_time, end_time)
```

The `(resource_id, start_time, end_time)` composite index enables O(log n) overlap detection — the system checks "is this resource free between T1 and T2?" without full table scans.

### Reminder Settings (from live data)

```json
{
  "active": true,
  "channels": { "email": true, "sms": true, "whatsapp": false },
  "offsets_hours": [48, 24, 2],
  "email": { "subject": "Appointment Reminder",
             "body": "Hello {patient_name}, your appointment is at {appointment_time}." },
  "sms":   { "message": "Reminder: {appointment_time} with {doctor_name} at {branch_name}." }
}
```

Reminders fire at 48h, 24h, and 2h before appointments across email and SMS channels (WhatsApp configured but not yet active).

