| `super_admin` | All 82 permissions | Full platform access |
| `admin` | 6 permissions (appointments + availability) | Scheduling-focused admin |
| `receptionist` | 3 permissions (view/create/edit appointments) | Front-desk only |

### 82 Permissions Across 24 Modules

Standard CRUD across all clinical modules plus specialised permissions:

- **`sign_report`** — gates clinician digital signature on final reports, separating result entry from report release
- **`generate_report_accounting`** — dedicated permission for accounting report generation
- **`view_availability` / `edit_availability`** — granular scheduling governance

The `sign_report` permission is architecturally significant — it enforces a two-step verification workflow between a technician entering results and a clinician releasing the final report.

