## 11. Schema Design Observations

### Strengths

| Pattern | Detail |
|---|---|
| Failover-ordered AI providers | `failover_order` enables deterministic fallback without code changes |
| AI result caching | `cache_ttl` on interpretations prevents redundant API calls for unchanged results |
| Consent timestamp | `consent_at` on usage logs creates an immutable per-call consent audit trail |
| White-label branding | `ai_branding_settings` fully decouples AI provider identity from patient UI |
| Covering index on appointments | Triple-column composite index optimises the most frequent scheduling query |
| Resource overlap index | `(resource_id, start_time, end_time)` enables O(log n) conflict detection |
| Commission rule engine | Time-bounded, plan-specific rules with first/recurring/per-report flags |
| Double-entry ledger | Every wallet credit linked to patient + subscription + payment + plan |
| Idempotency key on payments | `payment_transactions.idempotency_key` prevents duplicate charge processing |
| Webhook signature validation | `payment_webhook_events.signature_valid` flag with raw payload retained |

### Risks and Improvement Opportunities

| Issue | Severity | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|
| SMTP credentials in settings | High | Move to encrypted config or environment variable |
| `patients.dob` as varchar | Medium | Migrate to `date` type for SQL age calculations |
| Mixed FK types on `groups` | Medium | Align `patient_id`, `doctor_id` to `bigint UNSIGNED` |
| No UNIQUE on `ai_interpretations(result_id)` | Medium | Add constraint to prevent duplicate interpretations |
| 2FA codes in plaintext | Medium | Hash OTP codes; encrypt TOTP secrets at rest |
| `properties` empty on all activity logs | Low | Activity details not captured — investigate hook wiring |
| Duplicate `de` (German) in languages | Low | IDs 3 and 11 both have `iso = 'de'` — clean up duplicate |

