## 12. Analytical SQL Queries

### Q1: AI provider cost and error rate summary

```sql
SELECT
  provider,
  model,
  COUNT(*)                                                        AS total_calls,
  SUM(tokens_in + tokens_out)                                     AS total_tokens,
  SUM(cost_estimate)                                              AS total_cost_usd,
  AVG(latency_ms)                                                 AS avg_latency_ms,
  ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN status != 'ok' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0
        / COUNT(*), 2)                                            AS error_rate_pct
FROM ai_usage_logs
GROUP BY provider, model
ORDER BY total_cost_usd DESC;
```

### Q2: AI interpretation coverage across all test results

```sql
SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT gtr.id)                                          AS total_results,
  COUNT(DISTINCT ai.result_id)                                    AS results_with_ai,
  ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT ai.result_id) * 100.0
        / COUNT(DISTINCT gtr.id), 1)                             AS ai_coverage_pct,
  COUNT(DISTINCT aim.id)                                          AS total_marker_explanations
FROM group_test_results gtr
LEFT JOIN ai_interpretations ai        ON ai.result_id = gtr.id
LEFT JOIN ai_interpretation_markers aim ON aim.interpretation_id = ai.id;
```

### Q3: Patient subscription plan distribution

```sql
SELECT
  pp.name                                                         AS plan_name,
  pp.price                                                        AS price_usd,
  COUNT(ps.id)                                                    AS subscribers,
  SUM(CASE WHEN ps.status = 'active'    THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)       AS active,
  SUM(CASE WHEN ps.status = 'cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)       AS cancelled
FROM patient_plans pp
LEFT JOIN patient_subscriptions ps ON ps.plan_id = pp.id
GROUP BY pp.id, pp.name, pp.price
ORDER BY pp.price DESC;
```

### Q4: Doctor commission wallet health

```sql
SELECT
  d.name                                                          AS doctor,
  dw.current_balance,
  dw.pending_payout,
  COUNT(dl.id)                                                    AS ledger_entries,
  SUM(dl.amount)                                                  AS total_credited,
  SUM(CASE WHEN dpr.status = 'pending' THEN dpr.amount ELSE 0 END) AS pending_payout_amount
FROM doctors d
JOIN doctor_wallets dw              ON dw.doctor_id = d.id
LEFT JOIN doctor_wallet_ledgers dl  ON dl.doctor_id = d.id
LEFT JOIN doctor_payout_requests dpr ON dpr.doctor_id = d.id
GROUP BY d.id, d.name, dw.current_balance, dw.pending_payout
ORDER BY dw.current_balance DESC;
```

### Q5: Appointment funnel with wait and treatment time

```sql
SELECT
  COUNT(*)                                                         AS total_appointments,
  SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'confirmed'         THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)   AS confirmed,
  SUM(CASE WHEN checkin_status = 'arrived'   THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)   AS arrived,
  SUM(CASE WHEN checkin_status = 'done'      THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)   AS completed,
  SUM(CASE WHEN no_show_at IS NOT NULL       THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)   AS no_shows,
  ROUND(AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, arrived_at, in_room_at)), 1)    AS avg_wait_min,
  ROUND(AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, in_room_at, done_at)), 1)      AS avg_treatment_min
FROM appointments;
```

### Q6: AI spend attributed per patient

```sql
SELECT
  p.name                                                          AS patient_name,
  COUNT(al.id)                                                    AS ai_calls,
  SUM(al.tokens_in + al.tokens_out)                              AS total_tokens,
  SUM(al.cost_estimate)                                           AS total_ai_cost_usd,
  MIN(al.consent_at)                                              AS first_consent
FROM patients p
JOIN ai_usage_logs al ON al.patient_id = p.id
GROUP BY p.id, p.name
ORDER BY total_ai_cost_usd DESC;
```

### Q7: Reminder delivery funnel by channel

```sql
SELECT
  channel,
  COUNT(*)                                                          AS total_sent,
  SUM(CASE WHEN delivered_at IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)        AS delivered,
  SUM(CASE WHEN opened_at IS NOT NULL    THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)        AS opened,
  SUM(CASE WHEN clicked_at IS NOT NULL   THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)        AS clicked,
  ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN delivered_at IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)
        * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 1)                                     AS delivery_rate_pct
FROM appointment_reminders
GROUP BY channel;
```

